{"word":"ὀκνηρός","slug":"ὀκνηρός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ὀϰνηρός, ά, όν</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὀκνέω\">ὀκνέω</a></el>]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> ‘hesitant about doing <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ someth.\">someth.</a>’, <b>sluggish</b> (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> our ‘dragging one’s feet’) <b><a href='B:470 25:26'>Mt 25:26</a>; <a href='B:520 12:11'>Ro 12:11</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> in description of a thing with potential for causing reluctance, <b>bothersome, irksome <a href='B:570 3:1'>Phil 3:1</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ὀκνέω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ὀκταήμερος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}